(105, 'Vulnerability Management', '{\n \"title\": \"VULNERABILITY MANAGEMENT\",\n \"pages\": [\n  {\n   \"name\": \"PROVIDE ASSET LIST\",\n   \"elements\": [\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Description\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n     \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP SM2.6 Asset Registers</h6>\\n<b>Principle:</b> Important assets should be recorded in accurate and up-to-date asset registers.</br>\\n<b>Objective:</b> To help support risk-based decisions regarding the provision or use of assets (e.g. hardware, software, information, suppliers or operating environments), reduce the risk of information security being compromised by weaknesses in assets, protect them against loss, support development of contracts and meet compliance requirements for licensing.\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.1\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"How are assets tracked?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - All assets including information and their ownership by a designated part of the organisation shall be clearly identified and an inventory of all assets drawn up and maintained.\\nRisk - Lack of inventory of information assets with no defined owner and business value may lead to absence of accountability and creation of confusion in a case of security incident/disaster.\\nRecommendation - A formal asset management policy should be in place that includes the process to identify and maintain an inventory of critical assets with information on ownership, business value and security classification.\\n\\nA CMDB provides the best view of the IT environment if it has been implemented well. A well implemented CMDB would be the advisable ideal standard.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"CMDB\",\n       \"text\": \"CMDB\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Live list in the Management Console (e.g. AWS or Azure)\",\n       \"text\": \"Live list in the Management Console (e.g. AWS or Azure)\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"List somewhere e.g. Confluence or Github\",\n       \"text\": \"List somewhere e.g. Confluence or Github\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Unsure or they aren\'t\",\n       \"text\": \"Unsure or they aren\'t\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.1c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.2\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"minWidth\": \"\",\n     \"title\": \"Who owns the asset registry?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - All assets and their registry shall be documented and ownership should be defined to identify the responsibility and accountability for the management of these assets. \\nRisk - Without proper ownership it is difficult to manage assets and assign accountability.\\nRecommendation - A centralized asset registry shall be managed by a designated individual or a group.\\nA centralised Asset registry owned by IT or Operations is the advisable ideal standard.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"IT\",\n       \"text\": \"IT\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Operations\",\n       \"text\": \"Operations\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Corp IT\",\n       \"text\": \"Corp IT\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Dev\",\n       \"text\": \"Dev\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Security\",\n       \"text\": \"Security\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.2c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.3\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Are all assets for this platform in the asset list?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - All the assets shall be accounted for as per the asset management program.\\nRisk - Unaccounted and unmanaged assets possess a risk of being left behind for critical upgrades and updates.\\nRecommendations - All assets involved within the platform shall be maintained in the approved asset list.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ],\n     \"colCount\": 2\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.3c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.4\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"How often do you receive this list?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - An approved asset list shall be maintained and updated periodically and in cases of change in assets. The assets list shall be reviewed for any unaccounted / change assets.\\nRisk - Without regularly reviewed asset list, the organization may become vulnerable to external attacks that may affect the unmanaged assets.\\nRecommendation - A process shall be defined to review and monitor asset list periodically.\\n\\nA current asset list feeding directly into security tools ensures complete and timely coverage. This is the ideal standard.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Automatically\",\n       \"text\": \"Automatically\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.75\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Its \'live\' so when we like\",\n       \"text\": \"Its \'live\' so when we like\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable \"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"On demand when we ask\",\n       \"text\": \"On demand when we ask\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.25\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.4c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.5\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Is the Asset list accurate?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - All assets list shall be accurate and accuracy should be checked either with the help of an automated solutions or by manual audits.\\nRisk - Inaccurate asset list may lead to theft of assets, missing on critical updates and vulnerable systems.\\nRecommendation - A process shall be in place to check for accuracy of asset list.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Low confidence\",\n       \"text\": \"Low confidence\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.25\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.5c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.6\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"How is the Asset list kept up to date?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - All assets list shall be up to date and controls should be in place to maintain accuracy of the asset list.\\nRisk - Inaccurate asset list may lead to theft of assets, missing on critical updates and vulnerable systems.\\nRecommendation - A process or a  solutions shall be in place to check for inclusion of new assets in the asset list.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Automatic\",\n       \"text\": \"Automatic\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.75\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Manual\",\n       \"text\": \"Manual\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable \"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No List\",\n       \"text\": \"No List\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.6c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"text\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.7\",\n     \"title\": \"How many assets are there?\",\n     \"description\": \"Please provide a comprehensive details of all the physical assets involved in the project or provide a auto generated list of asset.\",\n     \"inputType\": \"number\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.1.7c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    }\n   ],\n   \"title\": \"Asset List Provision and Accuracy\"\n  },\n  {\n   \"name\": \"SEGMENT LIST\",\n   \"elements\": [\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Description\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n     \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP NC1.2 Physical Network Management</h6>\\n<b>Principle:</b> Networks (including voice networks) should be protected by physical controls and supported by accurate, up-to-date documentation and labelling of essential components.\\n </br>\\n<b>Objective:</b> To ensure that networks (including voice networks) are configured accurately and securely and provide employees with a clear statement of the security disciplines they are expected to follow.\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST - Not Applicable<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.03\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.2.1\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Who manages the Network Segments list?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Network Segments list shall be owned by a designated individual or a group to ensure prevention of any network changes.\\nRisk - Without ownership of network segments list, it is difficult for an organization to manage network access and prevent unauthorized changes,\\nRecommendation - An individual or a group shall be designated to manage the network segment list along with a process to ensure that no network changes occur without a proper change management process.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - <br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - <br>\\nPCI DSS - <br>\\nCIS Top 20 - <br>\\nCOBIT 5 - \",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Networks\",\n       \"text\": \"Networks\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"IT\",\n       \"text\": \"IT\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Other\",\n       \"text\": \"Other\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.25\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No one\",\n       \"text\": \"No one\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.2.1c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.2.2\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Do you have a current diagram of the Network environment?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - A network diagram is a graphical / pictorial representation of the organization\'s network infrastructure, connectivity and the assets involved. A network diagram shall always be maintained to identify point of failures and other critical devices. \\n\\nRisk - Absence of a network diagram may lead unmanaged network and inconsistent network security practices.\\nRecommendation - A network diagram shall be defined and maintained to ensure that all vulnerabilities and exceptions are identified.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - Not Applicable<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM2.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.03\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Partial\",\n       \"text\": \"Partial\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.2.2c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"VM.1.2.3\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"How is the diagram kept up to date?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Network Diagrams   shall be kept up to date in case of a change in the network setup (equipment or infrastructure). \\nRisk - Network Diagrams that are not updated poses a risk of improper management of network devices and connectivity.\\nRecommendation - A process/solutions shall be in place to ensure that network diagrams are updated as per the frequency defined by the leadership.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework -