",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n     \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP TM2.2 Security Incident Management Process</h6>\\n<b>Principle:</b> Information security incidents should be identified, responded to, recovered from, and followed up using an information security incident management process.</br>\\n<b>Objective:</b> To identify and resolve information security incidents quickly and effectively, minimise their business impact and reduce the risk of similar incidents occurring.\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.3.3<br>\\nNIST - DE.AE.2<br>\\nPCI DSS - RM10.2<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - APO04.01\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SM.3.3.1\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Do you have a defined and documented Security Incident Response Process?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Information security events shall be reported through appropriate communications channels as quickly as possible. All employees, contractors and third party users shall be made aware of their responsibility to report any information security events as quickly as possible. Security events and weaknesses are handled in a manner allowing timely corrective action to be taken.\\nRisk - Without a defined information security incident management policy and reporting procedure, formal acknowledgement, risk mitigation, and notification procedures may not be consistently implemented. \\nRecommendation - A formal information security incident management policy and reporting procedure should be put in place to minimize damage from incidents and malfunctions. This should include a process for reporting, escalating, investigating and resolving security incidents as quickly as possible. Additionally, all employees, contractors and third party users shall be made aware of their responsibility to report any information security events as quickly as possible.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.3.3<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.2<br>\\nPCI DSS - RM10.2<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - APO04.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SM.3.3.1c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SM.3.3.2\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Is the Incident process effective and adhered to?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Management responsibilities and procedures shall be established to ensure a quick, effective, and orderly response to information security incidents.\\nRisk - Without accountability and standard procedures for managing security incidents, adequate and timely resolution may not occur which could lead to compromise of data integrity and violation of contractual/legal requirements.\\nRecommendation - Management responsibilities and standard procedures in managing information security incidents should be clearly established, documented and communicated.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.3.3<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.2<br