(111, 'System Hardening', '{\n \"title\": \"SYSTEM HARDENING\",\n \"pages\": [\n  {\n   \"name\": \"OS HARDENING\",\n   \"elements\": [\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Description\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n     \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP PA1.2 Workstation Configuration</h6>\\n<b>Principle:</b> Workstation computers should be built using standard technical configurations and subject to security management practices to protect information against loss, theft and unauthorised disclosure.</br>\\n<b>Objective:</b> To ensure workstation computers do not impact the security of information stored on them or processed by them, and prevent unauthorised access to information in the event they are compromised, lost or stolen.\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 6.2.1<br>\\nNIST - PR.AC.2<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM1.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 2-2<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI10.01\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.1\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Is there a defined best practice OS hardening standard?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Operating Systems  shall be managed and controlled in order to protect the organizationfrom threats and to maintain security for the systems and applications using the network, including information in transit. \\nRisk - Systems may be vulnerable to attack if unused services are installed which may lead to data breach.\\nRecommendation - System baselines or system hardening guidelines should be documented for all critical systems.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 6.2.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - PR.AC.2<br>\\nPCI DSS - BM1.4<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 2-2<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI10.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes, meets PCI standards\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes, meets PCI standards\",\n       \"Score\": \"3\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Partially\",\n       \"text\": \"Partially\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.1c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.2\",\n     \"title\": \"What percentage of the systems in the Asset list are hardened?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Operating Systems  shall be managed and controlled in order to protect the organizationfrom threats and to maintain security for the systems and applications using the network, including information in transit. \\nRisk - Systems may be vulnerable to attack if unused services are installed which may lead to data breach.\\nRecommendation - System baselines or system hardening guidelines should be documented for all critical systems.\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"0\",\n       \"text\": \"0\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"10\",\n       \"text\": \"10\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.4\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"20\",\n       \"text\": \"20\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.8\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"30\",\n       \"text\": \"30\",\n       \"Score\": \"1.2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"40\",\n       \"text\": \"40\",\n       \"Score\": \"1.6\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"50\",\n       \"text\": \"50\",\n       \"Score\": \"2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"60\",\n       \"text\": \"60\",\n       \"Score\": \"2.4\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"70\",\n       \"text\": \"70\",\n       \"Score\": \"2.8\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"80\",\n       \"text\": \"80\",\n       \"Score\": \"3.2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"90\",\n       \"text\": \"90\",\n       \"Score\": \"3.6\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"100\",\n       \"text\": \"100\",\n       \"Score\": \"4\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      }\n     ],\n     \"colCount\": 5\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.2c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.3\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"HIPS (Host Intrusion Prevention System) configured on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Networks shall be managed and controlled in order to protect the organizationfrom threats and to maintain security for the systems and applications using the network, including information in transit. \\nRisk - Possibility of existing or emerging signatures going undetected which could result in the introduction of malware or access to the network by unauthorized individuals leading to data loss\\nRecommendation - HIPS should be deployed for internally facing networks.\\n\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 9.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - RM10.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-4<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.02\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"3\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.3c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.4\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"HIDS (Host Intrusion Detection System) configured on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Networks shall be managed and controlled in order to protect the organizationfrom threats and to maintain security for the systems and applications using the network, including information in transit. \\nRisk - Possibility of existing or emerging signatures going undetected which could result in the introduction of malware or access to the network by unauthorized individuals leading to data loss\\nRecommendation - HIDS should be deployed for internally facing networks.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 9.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - RM10.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-4<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.02\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.4c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.5\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"OSSEC agent installed on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - OSSEC is a scalable, multi-platform, open source Host-based Intrusion Detection System (HIDS). OSSEC agents are applications that regularly communicates with the HIDS and provides them information on non compliant policies and vulnerable systems\\nRisk - Without OSSEC agents, the HIDS/ HIPS server would not be able to identify vulnerable systems.\\nRecommendation - OSSEC agents should be installed and configured on all systems\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 9.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - RM10.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-4<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.02\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.5c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.6\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"FIM (File Integrity Monitoring) agent installed on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - File integrity monitoring (FIM) refers to an IT security process and technology that tests and checks operating system (OS), database, and application software files to determine whether or not they have been tampered with or corrupted.\\nRisk - Absence of a FIM system, it may be difficult to detect illicit activity, pinpoint unintended changes and meeting mandatory compliances.\\nRecommendation - FIM systems should be installed and configured on all systems\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 9.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - RM10.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-4<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.02\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.6c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.7\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Log collector agent installed on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Log collector agents are applications that communicate with the SIEM solution to provide logs\\nRisk - Without Log collector agents, SIEM may not collect all / proper logs to correlate or analyze logs for suspicious activity.\\nRecommendation - Log collectors  should be installed and configured on all systems\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.2<br>\\nPCI DSS - VM6.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 1-3<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS02.04\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.7c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.8\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Vulnerability scanner agent installed on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Vulnerability scanner agents are applications that scans the systems locally and communicates with the vulnerability scan server applications.\\nRisk - Without vulnerability scan agents, vulnerable systems may not be identified and may not be scanned for internal or external vulnerabilities.\\nRecommendation - Vulnerability Scan Agents should be installed and configured on all systems\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.6.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.RA.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - VM6.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - EDM03.02\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.8c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.9\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"AV or Anti Malware agent installed on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - AV or Anti Malware agents are critical in protecting individual systems by fetching updates, virus signatures and other important information.\\nRisk - Without AV or Anti Malware Agents, systems may not be patched with latest virus signatures and thus making the system vulnerable\\nRecommendation - AV or Anti Malware Agents  should be installed and configured on all systems\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.1.3<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.CM.4<br>\\nPCI DSS - VM6.2<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-10<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.9c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.10\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"DLP Agent installed on all assets?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Data Loss prevention (DLP) agents are applications that communicate with the enterprise DLP solution to update global policies and updates.\\nRisk - Without DLP agents, the DLP solutions may not be able to push policies and updated down to individual systems.\\nRecommendation - Without DLP agents, the DLP solutions may not be able to push policies and updated down to individual systems.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 11.1.2<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.3<br>\\nPCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-4<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - BAI08.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"0.5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.10c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"text\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.11\",\n     \"title\": \"What DLP agent do you use?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - There are no preferred vendors but the organization should consider the following factors while selecting a vendor : The providers credibility, compliance with organization\'s security policies, Due diligence of the provider, gartner quadrant etc\\nRisk - Selecting a vendor without proper diligence may lead to a provider with insufficient knowledge and skills to maintain a DLP Solution. This could prove catastrophic during monitoring or correlation of logs.\\nRecommendation - It is recommended that a vendor / provider / solution shall be selected based on the organizations\' objective, due diligence and availability of resources.\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.11c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.12\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"What Vulnerability Scanner do you use?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - There are no preferred vendors but the organization should consider the following factors while selecting a vendor : The providers credibility, compliance with organization\'s security policies, Due diligence of the provider, gartner quadrant etc\\nRisk - Selecting a vendor without proper diligence may lead to a provider with insufficient knowledge and skills to maintain a VM Solution. This could prove catastrophic during monitoring or correlation of logs.\\nRecommendation - It is recommended that a vendor / provider / solution shall be selected based on the organizations\' objective, due diligence and availability of resources.\\n\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.6.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.RA.1<br>\\nPCI DSS - VM6.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - EDM03.02\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Tenable\",\n       \"text\": \"Tenable\",\n       \"Score\": \"2\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Other\",\n       \"text\": \"Other\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"None\",\n       \"text\": \"None\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.12c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.13\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"What AV or Anti Malware do you use?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - There are no preferred vendors but the organization should consider the following factors while selecting a vendor : The providers credibility, compliance with organization\'s security policies, Due diligence of the provider, gartner quadrant etc\\nRisk - Selecting a vendor without proper diligence may lead to a provider with insufficient knowledge and skills to maintain a AV Solution. This could prove catastrophic during monitoring or correlation of logs.\\nRecommendation - It is recommended that a vendor / provider / solution shall be selected based on the organizations\' objective, due diligence and availability of resources.\\n\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.1.3<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.CM.4<br>\\nPCI DSS - VM6.2<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - CSC 7-10<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - DSS05.01\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Crowdstrike\",\n       \"text\": \"Crowdstrike\",\n       \"Score\": \"2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Other\",\n       \"text\": \"Other\",\n       \"Score\": \"1\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"None\",\n       \"text\": \"None\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.13c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250p