olution shall be selected based on the organizations\' objective, due diligence and availability of resources.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.15c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"text\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.16\",\n     \"title\": \"What HIPS (Host Intrusion Prevention System) do you use? e.g. Symantec DCS, Tripwire, etc\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - There are no preferred vendors but the organization should consider the following factors while selecting a vendor : The providers credibility, compliance with organization\'s security policies, Due diligence of the provider, gartner quadrant etc\\nRisk - Selecting a vendor without proper diligence may lead to a provider with insufficient knowledge and skills to maintain a HIPS Solution. This could prove catastrophic during monitoring or correlation of logs.\\nRecommendation - It is recommended that a vendor / provider / solution shall be selected based on the organizations\' objective, due diligence and availability of resources.\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.1.16c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    }\n   ],\n   \"title\": \"OS Hardening\"\n  },\n  {\n   \"name\": \"NETWORK SECURITY\",\n   \"elements\": [\n    {\n     \"type\": \"html\",\n     \"name\": \"Description\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n     \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP NC1.1 Network Device Configuration</h6>\\n<b>Principle:</b> Network devices should be configured to function as required, and to prevent unauthorised or incorrect updates.</br>\\n<b>Objective:</b>