ling and storage of information shall be established to protect this information from unauthorized disclosure or misuse. \\nRisk - Possibility of data loss if unencrypted hard disk drive is lost, stolen, incorrectly disposed of.\\nRecommendation - Desktops that have the ability to access/process/store, organizations Group data should have full disk encryption.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.GV.3<br>\\nPCI DSS - CD3.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - APO07.06\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Application/Database\",\n       \"text\": \"Application/Database\",\n       \"Score\": \"9\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"OS (File level encryption)\",\n       \"text\": \"OS (File level encryption)\",\n       \"Score\": \"4\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Basic HW\",\n       \"text\": \"Basic HW\",\n       \"Score\": \"2\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.1c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.2\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"How are the encryption keys managed?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Key management shall be in place to support the organizations use of cryptographic techniques.\\nRisk - Absence of a key management process could lead to the loss of or misuse of information assets.\\nRecommendation - The key management process should be defined, documented and implemented\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.GV.3<br>\\nPCI DSS - CD3.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - APO07.06\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"HSM (Hardware Security Model)\",\n       \"text\": \"HSM (Hardware Security Model)\",\n       \"Score\": \"5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Software HSM\",\n       \"text\": \"Software HSM\",\n       \"Score\": \"5\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.2c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.3\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Is sensitive data encrypted at rest on all hard drives?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Procedures for the handling and storage of information shall be established to protect this information from unauthorized disclosure or misuse. \\nRisk - Possibility of data loss if unencrypted hard disk drive is lost, stolen, incorrectly disposed of.\\nRecommendation - Desktops that have the ability to access/process/store, organizations Group data should have full disk encryption.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.GV.3<br>\\nPCI DSS - CD3.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - APO07.06\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"3\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.3c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.4\",\n     \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Are all communications and data transfers encrypted?\",\n     \"description\": \"Statement - Data should be encrypted while in transit between networks or the internet using protocals such as HTTPS / TLS 1.2 and others.\\nRisk - Unencrypted data in transit is vulnerable to attacks such as sniffing, man in the middle attacks and data theft.\\nRecommendation - Encryption protocols shall be configured to ensure that every data packet moving between the networks follows strong encryption algorithm.\",\n     \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n     \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks</h6>\\nISO/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>\\nNIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.GV.3<br>\\nPCI DSS - CD3.1<br>\\nCIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>\\nCOBIT 5 - APO07.06\",\n     \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n     \"choices\": [\n      {\n       \"value\": \"Yes\",\n       \"text\": \"Yes\",\n       \"Score\": \"3\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n      },\n      {\n       \"value\": \"No\",\n       \"text\": \"No\",\n       \"Score\": \"0\",\n       \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n      }\n     ]\n    },\n    {\n     \"type\": \"comment\",\n     \"name\": \"SH.4.5.4c\",\n     \"width\": \"250px\",\n     \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n     \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n     \"title\": \"Comment\",\n     \"hideNumber\": true,\n     \"cols\": 40\n    }\n   ],\n   \"title\": \"Data Encrypted\"\n  }\n ],\n \"showQuestionNumbers\": \"off\",\n \"questionDescriptionLocation