        {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC2.3 Business Continuity Testing<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Business continuity plans and arrangements should be tested on a regular basis.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To provide assurance that business continuity plans and arrangements will work as required, so that critical business processes can resume within predefined timescales.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 17.1.3<br>NIST - PR.IP.9<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.04\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC1.2 Business Continuity Programme<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> A business continuity programme should be established, which includes developing a resilient technical infrastructure, creating a crisis management capability, and coordinating and maintaining business continuity plans and arrangements across the organisation.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To enable the organisation to withstand the prolonged unavailability of critical information, business applications and related technical infrastructure, and provide individuals with a documented set of actions to perform in the event of a disaster or emergency.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 6.1.1<br>NIST - ID.BE.5<br>PCI DSS - BM2.4<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.05\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.1.8\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Has a business impact analysis (BIA) been performed for mission critical and auxiliary applications?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Events that can cause interruptions to business processes shall be identified, along with the probability and impact of such interruptions and their consequences for information security.Risk - Business continuity and\\/or disaster recovery plans may not satisfy business requirements.Recommendation - Implement a documented and approved process to ensure that Business Impact Analysis(BIA) is performed on all services and systems supporting Group project(s).\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 14.1.1<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.RA.4<br>PCI DSS - IS12.2<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-8<br>COBIT 5 - EDM02.03\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Yes\",\n                            \"text\": \"Yes\",\n                            \"Score\": \"4\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Partially\",\n                            \"text\": \"Partially\",\n                            \"Score\": \"2\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"No\",\n                            \"text\": \"No\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.1.8c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"DISASTER RECOVERY\",\n            \"title\": \"Disaster Recovery\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC2.1 Business Continuity Planning<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Business continuity plans should be developed and documented to support critical business processes throughout the organisation.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To provide relevant individuals with a documented set of actions to perform in the event of a disaster or emergency affecting business applications and technical infrastructure, enabling critical business processes to be resumed within agreed timescales.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.2.1<br>NIST - Not Applicable<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-8<br>COBIT 5 - BAI07.06\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC2.3 Business Continuity Testing<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Business continuity plans and arrangements should be tested on a regular basis.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To provide assurance that business continuity plans and arrangements will work as required, so that critical business processes can resume within predefined timescales.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 17.1.3<br>NIST - PR.IP.9<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.04\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.2.9\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"For all Business and Mission critical applications, how often is restoration and testing of backup performed ?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - DRP shall be tested and updated regularly, at a minimum annually, to ensure that they are up to date and effective.\\\"Risk - Without periodically testing DR plan, timely recovery of business processes, information technology systems, and related information assets may not be possible.Recommendation - DR should be tested regularly to ensure that it effectively meets recovery point and time objectives in line with the business needs.\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 17.1.3<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - PR.IP.9<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.04\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Annually\",\n                            \"text\": \"Annually\",\n                            \"Score\": \"4\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Ad hoc (less often than annually)\",\n                            \"text\": \"Ad hoc (less often than annually)\",\n                            \"Score\": \"2\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Not sure\",\n                            \"text\": \"Not sure\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.2.9c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"ARCHITECTURE & RESILIENCE\",\n            \"title\": \"Architecture & Resilience\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP SY2.1 Service Level Agreements<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Computer and network services that support critical business processes and applications should only be obtained from service providers capable of providing required security controls, and be supported by documented contracts or service level agreements.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To define the business requirements for providers of any computer or network services, including those for information security, and to ensure they are met.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>NIST - Not Applicable<br>PCI DSS - BM1.3<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 7-2<br>COBIT 5 - APO09.01\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP SD2.2 System Design<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Information security requirements for systems under development should be considered when designing systems.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To produce live systems based on sound design principles which have security functionality built in, enable controls to be incorporated easily, are able to withstand malicious attacks, and help ensure that no security weaknesses are introduced during the build process.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 9.2.3<br>NIST - ID.RA.1<br>PCI DSS - VM6.3<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 18-1<br>COBIT 5 - BAI01.04\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BA1.2 Web Application Protection<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Specialised procedural and technical controls should be applied to web applications, web content and websites.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To ensure that the increased risks associated with web applications are minimised.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 10.1.1<br>NIST - Not Applicable<br>PCI DSS - BM2.3<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 9-4<br>COBIT 5 - DSS06.01\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP SD2.1 Specifications of Requirements<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> System requirements (including those for information security) should be documented in the business requirements and agreed before detailed design commences.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To ensure that information security requirements are treated as an integral part of business requirements, fully considered and approved.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 11.2.7<br>NIST - ID.AM.1<br>PCI DSS - VM6.3<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - APO04.04\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP IR1.2 Information Risk Assessment - Methodology<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Information risk assessments should be undertaken using systematic and structured methodologies.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To make information risk assessments effective, easy to conduct and consistent throughout the organisation and to produce a clear picture of key information risks.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>NIST - ID.GV.4<br>PCI DSS - IS12.2<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - EDM03.01\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP SM1.1 Information Security Policy<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> A comprehensive, documented information security policy should be produced and communicated to all individuals with access to the organisation\'s information and systems.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To document the governing body\'s direction on and commitment to information security, and communicate it to all relevant individuals.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>NIST - ID.GV.1<br>PCI DSS - CD4.2<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - APO01.03\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC2.3 Business Continuity Testing<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Business continuity plans and arrangements should be tested on a regular basis.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To provide assurance that business continuity plans and arrangements will work as required, so that critical business processes can resume within predefined timescales.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 17.1.3<br>NIST - PR.IP.9<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.04\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.3.8c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"text\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.3.8\",\n                    \"title\": \"What is the uptime SLA offered to our customers?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Service Level Agreements are an organizaned and mutually agreed way to define and identify the turn around time and action on incidents and the following process.Risk - Without accountability and standard procedures for managing security incidents, adequate and timely resolution may not occur which could lead to compromise of data integrity and violation of contractual\\/legal requirements.Recommendation - Management responsibilities and standard procedures in managing information security incidents should be clearly established, documented and communicated.\"\n                }\n            ]\n        }\n    ]\n}', '2021-02-10 03:11:36', '2021-02-10 04:46:40');
