(10, 3, 58, 113, '{\n    \"title\": \"AVAILABILITY\",\n    \"pages\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"BUSINESS CONTINUITY\",\n            \"title\": \"Business Continuity\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC1.1 Business Continuity Strategy<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> A business continuity strategy covering the whole organisation should be established, which promotes the need for business continuity management, embeds business continuity management into the organisation\'s culture, and is implemented in the form of a business continuity programme.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To align business continuity goals with the organisation\'s business goals, provide resilience against disruption and minimise impact to the organisation in the event of a disaster or emergency.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 14.2.3<br>NIST - Not Applicable<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.01\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC2.1 Business Continuity Planning<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Business continuity plans should be developed and documented to support critical business processes throughout the organisation.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To provide relevant individuals with a documented set of actions to perform in the event of a disaster or emergency affecting business applications and technical infrastructure, enabling critical business processes to be resumed within agreed timescales.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.2.1<br>NIST - Not Applicable<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-8<br>COBIT 5 - BAI07.06\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP IR2.2 Business Impact Assessment<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> The potential realistic and worst-case business impact (should critical or sensitive information in the target environment be compromised) should be determined for different categories of impact (e.g. financial, operational, legal and regulatory compliance, reputational and health and safety).<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To determine the business impact that business owners are willing to accept in the event information in the target environments is compromised; and agree the requirements for protecting the confidentiality, integrity and availability of that information.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 14.1.1<br>NIST  - ID.RA.4<br>PCI DSS - IS12.2<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-8<br>COBIT 5 - EDM02.03\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC2.3 Business Continuity Testing<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Business continuity plans and arrangements should be tested on a regular basis.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To provide assurance that business continuity plans and arrangements will work as required, so that critical business processes can resume within predefined timescales.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 17.1.3<br>NIST - PR.IP.9<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 19-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.04\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP BC1.2 Business Continuity Programme<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> A business continuity programme should be established, which includes developing a resilient technical infrastructure, creating a crisis management capability, and coordinating and maintaining business continuity plans and arrangements across the organisation.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To enable the organisation to withstand the prolonged unavailability of critical information, business applications and related technical infrastructure, and provide individuals with a documented set of actions to perform in the event of a disaster or emergency.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"visible\": false,\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 6.1.1<br>NIST - ID.BE.5<br>PCI DSS - BM2.4<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - DSS04.05\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"AV.6.1.6\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"How often are the components of the BCP reviewed and updated as needed to reflect change?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Plans shall be developed and implemented to maintain or restore operations and ensure availability of information at the required level and in the required time scales following interruption to, or failure of, critical business processes.Risk - Without business continuity plans, teams will not be able to limit losses caused by disruptions to critical business operations which could result in inefficient and ineffective recovery.Recommendation 