<h6>ISF SoGP PA1.2 Workstation Configuration<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Workstation computers should be built using standard technical configurations and subject to security management practices to protect information against loss, theft and unauthorised disclosure.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To ensure workstation computers do not impact the security of information stored on them or processed by them, and prevent unauthorised access to information in the event they are compromised, lost or stolen.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 6.2.1<br>NIST - PR.AC.2<br>PCI DSS - BM1.4<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 2-2<br>COBIT 5 - BAI10.01\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"SH.4.1.7\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Log collector agent installed on all assets?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Log collector agents are applications that communicate with the SIEM solution to provide logsRisk - Without Log collector agents, SIEM may not collect all \\/ proper logs to correlate or analyze logs for suspicious activity.Recommendation - Log collectors  should be installed and configured on all systems\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 12.1.1<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - DE.AE.2<br>PCI DSS - VM6.1<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 1-3<br>COBIT 5 - DSS02.04\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n               