n - Desktops that have the ability to access\\/process\\/store, organizations Group data should have full disk encryption.\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.GV.3<br>PCI DSS - CD3.1<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - APO07.06\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Yes\",\n                            \"text\": \"Yes\",\n                            \"Score\": \"3\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"No\",\n                            \"text\": \"No\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"SH.4.5.3c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"DATA ENCRYPTED\",\n            \"title\": \"Data Encrypted\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP IM1.2 Information Privacy<\\/h6>Principle Responsibility for managing information privacy should be established and information security controls applied for handling personally identifiable information (i.e. information that can be used to identify an individual person).<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To prevent personal information about individuals being used in an inappropriate manner and ensure compliance with legal and regulatory requirements for information privacy.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>NIST - ID.GV.3<br>PCI DSS - CD3.1<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - APO07.06\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"SH.4.5.4\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Are all communications and data transfers encrypted?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Data should be encrypted while in transit between networks or the internet using protocals such as HTTPS \\/ TLS 1.2 and others.Risk - Unencrypted data in transit is vulnerable to attacks such as sniffing, man in the middle attacks and data theft.Recommendation - Encryption protocols shall be configured to ensure that every data packet moving between the networks follows strong encryption algorithm.\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 5.1.1<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.GV.3<br>PCI DSS - CD3.1<br>CIS Top 20 - Not Applicable<br>COBIT 5 - APO07.06\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\