(25, 3, 13, 105, '{\n    \"title\": \"VULNERABILITY MANAGEMENT\",\n    \"pages\": [\n        {\n            \"name\": \"ASSET DISCOVERY\",\n            \"title\": \"Asset Discovery\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP SM2.6 Asset Registers<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Important assets should be recorded in accurate and up-to-date asset registers.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To help support risk-based decisions regarding the provision or use of assets (e.g. hardware, software, information, suppliers or operating environments), reduce the risk of information security being compromised by weaknesses in assets, protect them against loss, support development of contracts and meet compliance requirements for licensing.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>NIST - ID.AM.1<br>PCI DSS - BM2.4<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>COBIT 5 - BAI09.01\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"VM.1.3.2\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Is there a way to compare the results to the asset list?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Asset Discovery is a method to identify devices that added or modified within the network.Risk - Without a proper asset discovery mechanism unauthorized assets may be connected to the network.Recommendation - Discovered assets shall be compared to the actual asset list to look for discrepancies.\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 8.1.1<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>PCI DSS - BM2.4<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>COBIT 5 - BAI09.01\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Yes, Automated\",\n                            \"text\": \"Yes, Automated\",\n                            \"Score\": \"12\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Yes, Manually\",\n                            \"text\": \"Yes, Manually\",\n                            \"Score\": \"9\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Partial\",\n                            \"text\": \"Partial\",\n                            \"Score\": \"4.5\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"VM.1.3.2c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"EXTERNAL COVERAGE\",\n            \"title\": \"External Coverage\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF SoGP PA1.5 Specialised Computing Equipment and Devices<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Specialised computing equipment and devices should be identified, categorised and protected by security arrangements that are tailored to these devices.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To ensure specialised computing equipment and devices do not impact the security of information stored on them or processed by them, and prevent unauthorised access to information in the event they are compromised, lost or stolen.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - Not Applicable<br>NIST - ID.AM.1<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS05.03\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"VM.1.4.1\",\n                    \"useDisplayValuesInTitle\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"How often are external scans conducted on assets?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - Timely information about technical vulnerabilities of information systems being used shall be obtained; the organization\'s exposure to such vulnerabilities evaluated; and appropriate measures taken to address the associated risk.Risk - Information security weaknesses that are difficult to detect may exist which could lead to data loss or disruption of servicesRecommendation - Regular vulnerability management scans should be carried out at least monthly or after a change in the environment.\",\n                    \"descriptionLocation\": \"underInput\",\n                    \"Framework\": \"<h6>Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - Not Applicable<br>NIST Cybersecurity Framework - ID.AM.1<br>PCI DSS - Not Applicable<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 1-1<br>COBIT 5 - DSS05.03\",\n                    \"commentText\": \"enter here\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Weekly Automated\",\n                            \"text\": \"Weekly Automated\",\n                            \"Score\": \"5\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Monthly Automated\",\n                            \"text\": \"Monthly Automated\",\n                            \"Score\": \"5\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Quarterly Automated\",\n                            \"text\": \"Quarterly Automated\",\n                            \"Score\": \"5\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Ad Hoc\",\n                            \"text\": \"Ad Hoc\",\n                            \"Score\": \"2\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"Never\",\n                            \"text\": \"Never\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        }\n                    ]\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"VM.1.4.1c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                }\n            ]\n        },\n        {\n            \"name\": \"ASV COVERAGE\",\n            \"title\": \"ASV Coverage\",\n            \"elements\": [\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Description\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"600px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>ISF S0GP TM1.2 Security Event Logging<\\/h6><b>Principle:<\\/b> Important security-related events should be recorded in logs, stored centrally, protected against unauthorised change and analysed on a regular basis.<\\/br><b>Objective:<\\/b> To help identify threats that may lead to an information security incident, maintain the integrity of important security-related information and support forensic investigations.\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"html\",\n                    \"name\": \"Frameworks\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"html\": \"<h6>Associated Frameworks<\\/h6>ISO\\/IEC 27002:2013 - 9.2.5<br>NIST - PR.PT.1<br>PCI DSS - VM5.2<br>CIS Top 20 - CSC 1-3<br>COBIT 5 - BAI08.05\"\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"radiogroup\",\n                    \"name\": \"VM.1.6.1\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"\",\n                    \"title\": \"What percentage of PCI assets are covered by authenticated scans?\",\n                    \"description\": \"Statement - The Payment Card Industry mandates that information processing assets involved in accessing, processing or storing cardholder data must be scanned for authentication and vulnerabilities by an Approved Scanning Vendor, mostly by a Independent Third PartyRisk - If assets that handles cardholder data are not scanned on a regular basis may lead to compromise of critical information and could result in non compliance with PCI standards.Recommendations - All assets handling cardholder data should be scanned by an ASV as per the defined frequency and a record be maintained to ensure compliance.\",\n                    \"choices\": [\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"0\",\n                            \"text\": \"0\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"10\",\n                            \"text\": \"10\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0.4\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"20\",\n                            \"text\": \"20\",\n                            \"Score\": \"0.8\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"30\",\n                            \"text\": \"30\",\n                            \"Score\": \"1.2\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"40\",\n                            \"text\": \"40\",\n                            \"Score\": \"1.6\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"50\",\n                            \"text\": \"50\",\n                            \"Score\": \"2\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Non-Standard\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"60\",\n                            \"text\": \"60\",\n                            \"Score\": \"2.4\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"70\",\n                            \"text\": \"70\",\n                            \"Score\": \"2.8\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Acceptable\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"80\",\n                            \"text\": \"80\",\n                            \"Score\": \"3.2\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"90\",\n                            \"text\": \"90\",\n                            \"Score\": \"3.6\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        },\n                        {\n                            \"value\": \"100\",\n                            \"text\": \"100\",\n                            \"Score\": \"4\",\n                            \"Standard\": \"Ideal\"\n                        }\n                    ],\n                    \"colCount\": 5\n                },\n                {\n                    \"type\": \"comment\",\n                    \"name\": \"VM.1.6.1c\",\n                    \"width\": \"250px\",\n                    \"minWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"maxWidth\": \"250px\",\n                    \"startWithNewLine\": false,\n                    \"title\": \"Comment\",\n                    \"hideNumber\": true,\n                    \"cols\": 40\n                }\n            ]\n        }\n    ]\n}', '2021-02-16 06:26:44', '20